    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="456"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/447a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Commissioner of Docks and Ferries of New York City</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hulbert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1918</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your letter of the 21st instant<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d456fn1">Not printed.</note> you are advised that the Dutch
                    ships now lying idle in New York Harbor will very soon be freed, as the
                    negotiations which are being carried on by the Department of State and the War
                    Trade Board are now close to a successful termination. I think it is only a
                    matter of a very few days before all the vessels will be moving either to dry
                    dock or to sea</p>
                <p>Thanking you for your interest in the matter,</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
